=Description=

"The World Social Web Dialogue (WSWD) is a cross-website and cross-language global online dialogue. The aim is to incite and develop new, peripheral Internet standards and protocols as well as new information technologies which 1. correspond to the needs of those people, organisations, initiatives, institutions and social businesses committed to making the world a more socially and ecologically just place and 2. provide those people suffering from poverty and oppression with modern tools so that they can free themselves independently or through the support of other people."

